if (hasItem("tape 6")){
play("*\*TAPE RECORDER SFX\*\*\n\n KINDRA: \"I had the dream again. I’m in a world made of metal buildings, towering straight up into the clouds – there are streets crowded with strange looking people. Electric lights and sounds fill the air, and in the moment it is so vivid...so foreign, yet familiar.  I recognize words - the names of places and things.  I see machines made of pure, suspended light. Father, says it’s the future I’m seeing – the visions, another side effect of living here in liminal space. It’s all so real, so...present. If that’s the future, how do I know that now...is even now? Ugh, I hate this place.\"")
}else{
    callAction("take", "tape 6")
}

if (hasItem("tape 22")){
play("*\*TAPE RECORDER SFX\*\*\n\n KINDRA: \"Father is hiding something. Why else keep his lab secret from me? Whenever I ask to see it, he says “it’s only for those who can move the hands of time.” But I’m his daughter, why not teach me? There is something tucked away in the corners of my mind but he refuses to help me access it.  And why is his memory so much better than ours? Is it because he spends such much time outside of the Nexus, in real time? What if I could just get closer to the temporal barrier?  Maybe then I would start to remember – I don't know…but I have to try it. If he won’t show me where he keeps the doors of time, I’ll have to find it myself.\"")
}else{
    callAction("take", "tape 22")
}

if (hasItem("tape 17")){
play("*\*TAPE RECORDER SFX\*\*\n\n KINDRA: \"Ok, quick, before I forget, Father has a secret room hidden somewhere – right here in the mansion! Archie told me he saw it once, but of course he can’t remember where. Thank god for Archie, he’s the only one that really seems to care about getting out of this place, about having a future, any future. This morning I asked father: if the Nexus is so bad for my mind, then why don’t we just leave? But he says it’s not safe for me out there in the non-liminal, not until he finishes his research – and that what he’s doing will help me – help everyone! I don’t know what he means by that.  Okay, remember, tomorrow you’re supposed to help pick out a gift for Cosette. Something pretty, I think.\"")
}else{
    callAction("take", "tape 17")
}

if (hasItem("tape 24")){
play("*\*TAPE RECORDER SFX\*\*\n\n KINDRA: \"It’s all a lie. The bastard has been lying to me the whole time. How long have I been here? Is this the first time I’ve learned the truth? That he’s not my father but my kidnapper? That I have been kept here not against my will, but against my very self! My identity! The time door seems to emanate pulses of linear energy, the nearer I approached it, the more my memories returned in jolting waves of clarity. Staring into the vortex, I could see the future...my past. I could see my team unearthing the stone from its millennia-old resting place, its runic symbols radiant with the unclassifiable, space-distorting energy our LIGO had detected. Years and years of testing and obsessive experimentation, and finally that last night. The one that opened the door for him. He can’t know that I’ve found out, but I can’t afford to wait until I forget again. I must find and activate the rune, it’s the only safe way through the time rift.\"")

}else{
    callAction("take", "tape 24")
}

